# Environment configuration for allpets-frontend (7.9).
# Copy to .env.local for local dev (.env.local is gitignored). In CI/prod these are
# repo *variables* — none are secrets; all three origins are public.
#
# TWO KINDS OF VAR:
#   • NEXT_PUBLIC_*  — inlined into the bundle at BUILD time. Changing one requires a
#     REBUILD, not just a redeploy (common gotcha). CI (15.3) passes them as
#     --build-arg → ARG/ENV in the Dockerfile (7.8) before `pnpm build`.
#   • API_BASE       — SERVER-ONLY runtime env, changeable WITHOUT a rebuild (plain
#     container env). Never exposed to the browser.
#
# NOTE: marketing content is file-based (typed TS + MDX, Epic 8) — there is NO
# content-API env var.

# --- Server-only (runtime, no rebuild needed) ---
# Spring backend base (Epic 20). The same-origin /api/contact + /api/reviews proxy
# route handlers fetch this host SERVER-SIDE; the browser never calls it directly.
# May be an internal cluster URL when running in-cluster.
API_BASE=https://api.allpets.skpodduturi.dev

# --- Public (NEXT_PUBLIC_*, build-time inlined → change ⇒ rebuild) ---
# Cal.com embed origin (Epic 6/9) — the embed calOrigin.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CALCOM_URL=https://book.allpets.skpodduturi.dev
# Plausible site domain (Epic 11).
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=allpets.skpodduturi.dev
# Plausible analytics script URL (self-hosted Plausible CE host).
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_SCRIPT_URL=https://analytics.allpets.skpodduturi.dev/js/script.js
